## 🏗️ PARA Structure

This repository uses the [PARA method](https://fortelabs.com/blog/para/) for knowledge organization:

```
obsd/
├── Projects/          # Active projects with clear goals
├── Areas/             # Ongoing areas of responsibility
├── Resources/         # Reference materials and external content
│   ├── X/             # X/Twitter link analysis
│   ├── GitHub/        # GitHub repo analysis
│   ├── 📖 Technical Docs/  # Technical documentation
│   └── 🦞 Lobster Diary/   # Daily conversation summaries
└── Archives/          # Archived historical content
```

## 🤖 OpenClaw Automation

Powered by **OpenClaw** for intelligent automation:

- **URL Analysis**: Send X/Twitter or GitHub links for automatic analysis and categorization
- **QMD Local Semantic Search**: Zero-cost, privacy-first local embeddings and retrieval
- **Lobster Diary**: Auto-generated daily conversation summaries
- **Inspiration Library**: 4-dimension evaluation framework (value clarity, timeline, perception, discovery)

### Usage

```bash
# Send a link to OpenClaw
https://x.com/i/status/123456789
https://github.com/owner/repo

# Automatically get structured analysis saved to the correct directory
```

## 🔁 GitHub Sync Configuration

- **Auto Sync**: GitHub Sync plugin enabled with automatic sync on load
- **Sync Interval**: Every 1 minute for real-time backup
- **Version Control**: All note changes tracked in Git history
- **Cloud Backup**: GitHub as reliable cloud storage
- **Collaboration Ready**: Supports potential future collaboration

## 🚀 Quick Start

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/gandli/obsd.git
   ```

2. **Open in Obsidian**
   - Open Obsidian app
   - Select "Open folder as vault"
   - Choose the cloned `obsd` folder

3. **Start using**
   - Create new notes or edit existing ones
   - Organize content using PARA structure
   - Send links to OpenClaw for automatic analysis

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Core Tool**: [Obsidian](https://obsidian.md) - Powerful knowledge management app
- **Knowledge Method**: [PARA](https://fortelabs.com/blog/para/) - Personal knowledge management framework
- **Automation Engine**: [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai) - AI assistant framework
- **Local Search**: [QMD](https://github.com/tobilu/qmd) - Local embeddings and semantic search
- **Sync Plugin**: [GitHub Sync](https://github.com/denolehov/obsidian-github-sync) - Automatic Git sync

## 📊 Core Plugins

Key Obsidian plugins enabled:
- **Graph View** - Visualize knowledge connections
- **Backlinks** - Discover related content
- **Canvas** - Mind maps and visualizations
- **Daily Notes** - Daily journaling and reflection
- **Templates** - Standardized note formats
- **Command Palette** - Quick access to features

## 🎯 Use Cases

- **Knowledge Capture**: Quickly save and analyze external information
- **Project Management**: Track creative projects and development tasks
- **Learning Notes**: Technical learning and research records
- **Life Management**: Health, parenting, daily tasks
- **Inspiration Collection**: Creative ideas and discoveries

## 🔒 Privacy & Security

- **Local First**: All sensitive data stays local
- **Selective Sync**: Only sync non-sensitive reference materials
- **Version Control**: Git provides complete change history
- **Privacy Separation**: Work and personal content managed separately

